data.description: *Move in Ready *Recently renovated, historic pre 1900s 3 bedroom, 1 bath Toll gate house set on 4 green acres w/ a fully stocked fishing/livestock pond & out waterer, full tobacco barn w/stalls, large work shop & separate garage/storage building in beautiful Bourbon county countryside 15 min. From Lexington, Georgetown, Winchester, farmers market & apple orchards. House stands on  the original stone foundation & rough cut, true spec lumber. 2 large bedrooms are 20' by 20' with 16' by 6' walk in closet. 3rd is standard size. Bathroom renovated, fully tiled shower w/bench. Kitchen renovatiion for an open floor plan to the living room.  Adjacent driveway and privacy wall added to the property.  This farm has a long history with the current owners and those who come before.  Many animals have called this land home and enjoyed the colorful seasons and rising/setting sun. The strong bones and intricate beauty of this property remain timeless and withstanding the many lives it has sheltered. A perfect set up for homesteading and making your own beloved space. Fully fenced / Hardwood floors. VA assumable Loan option available. Call Lisa 859 314-1307 to view.
